race.comment: KAKADU SUNSET (8) didn't have a great deal of luck when fifth to JELLICIOUS last time out. Enjoys a 3kgs weight swing today. Will race closer in the small field and looms as the logical threat. JOLLY GOOD FELLOW (3) reacted positively to a host of gear changes last time out when runner-up in a BM85 over 1300m at Bathurst. Can improve further at just the third run of the prep. Last start Kembla maiden winner IN AND OUT (7) tackles a far tougher assignment today but he is improving with racing and cannot be dismissed entirely. MAYBE MOET (9) probably isn't up to this but in the small field can sneak into the frame.
